context: <user>  I need a plane. Can you find one for me? Preferably a round trip. I need to be back on the 14th of this month and want premium economy seats. <system>  Sure. What day are you going? <user>  The 12th. Also, I need tickets for four. <system>  What city are you going to? And which city are you departing from? <user>  I'm going to ATL from Las Vegas. <system>  There's a Southwest Airlines plane which departs at 6:25 pm and costs $437. The flight which brings you back departs at 6:30 am. <user>  What station does the plane go to? And which one does it leave from? <system>  The plane goes from McCarran International Airport to Hartsfield-Jackson International Airport.<user>  Perfect. Could you reserve some seats for me? <system>  4 premium economy tickets for the Southwest Airlines flight from Las Vegas to Atlanta which leaves on March 12th at 6:25 pm, with a return flight which departs at 6:30 am on March 14th. Is that correct?<user>  That's right. <system>  I have reserved your seats.<user>  Can you also find me something interesting to do while I'm there? <system>  Sure. What kind of activity are you looking for? A music concert? A sports game? Or something else?<user>  I'd love to see a concert on the 13th of this month. <system>  How about going to see Emmylou Harris at Atlanta Symphony Orchestra?<user>  Awesome. Thanks for your help, I don't need anything else. <system>
